org.starhope.appius.user.events
Class EventType

java.lang.Object
  org.starhope.appius.util.SimpleDataRecord<EventType>
      org.starhope.appius.user.events.EventType
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.whirlycott.cache.Cacheable, Serializable, Comparable<EventType>, CastsToJSON, CTime, DataRecord, HasSubversionRevision
public class EventType
extends SimpleDataRecord<EventType>
implements CastsToJSON

An EventType is a type of event in which an user can participate. Examples might include playing a game or minigame, or encountering a specific treasure in the game world. Any event can yield an item (see InventoryItem) or a medal (see MedalType), as well as a certain amount of game currency (see Currency). When an user participates in an event, they will have an EventRecord indicating when it began, ended, and the results thereof.

XXX: currency support is mostly non-functional. 

 ALTER TABLE eventTypes ADD COLUMN frequencyLimit DECIMAL(2,0) UNSIGNED NOT NULL DEFAULT 99;
 ALTER TABLE eventTypes ADD COLUMN frequencyPeriod DECIMAL(6,0) UNSIGNED NOT NULL DEFAULT 1;

startEvent

public EventRecord startEvent(AbstractUser user)
                       throws AlreadyExistsException
Start an event for the user, of this type. Should throw exceptions if the event can't be started for some reason, e.g. frequency period enforcement

Parameters:
user - The user starting the event
Returns:
the event record created
Throws:
AlreadyExistsException - if the event has been performed already at (or more than) the limit for a given time period. The general response to the user should reflect something to the effect of “this event cannot be performed again, now” or suppress notification of the event altogether.
